Preheat oven to 375 degrees F. Drizzle juice over fillets. Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper. Heat butter or margarine in skillet. Saute celery and scallions in butter for 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Combine celery, scallion, and butter mixture with cucumber, cracker crumbs, sage, and remaining salt and pepper. Add hot water and toss with a fork to blend. Spread 2 tablespoons of cracker mixture on each fillet and roll up. Fasten securely with toothpicks. Place fillets in baking dish. Pour about 2 tablespoons of hot water around them, and brush with melted butter or margarine. Pack remaining dressing into a greased 1 quart casserole; cover casserole, and bake fillets and extra stuffing at 375 degrees F for 25 minutes. Spoon stuffing onto heated platter. Arrange fillets over stuffing. Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with lemon slices and parsley.